      "updated_at": "2026-05-30T18:41:04Z",
      "author_association": "NONE",
      "body": "Hello @willcl-ark, WSL is still VM based build, and MSYS2 runs on native-like environment with native Windows path support which means you don't need to move around to VM to debug and edit source code on both locations.\r\n\r\nAnd yeah MSYS2 is far from niche, it is built in with Github Actions on windows-latest env, and it should be able to support any GCC compile jobs while WSL would stall on some jobs ( yes, WSL is still buggy with my experience )",
      "user": {
        "login": "quadcpu",
        "id": 252797008,
